# C/C++

- Formatting follows `.clang-format` (`BasedOnStyle: Google`). Prefer running the formatter over manual spacing edits.
- Prefer RAII and value ownership clarity; document raw pointer ownership/lifetime in headers.
- Use `const` aggressively for inputs and methods that do not mutate state.
- Prefer standard library containers and algorithms before custom memory management.
- Keep headers minimal: include what you use, forward declare when it meaningfully reduces coupling.
- Avoid macros for constants or functions; use `constexpr`, `enum class`, or inline functions.
